-- Man Group down 5 pct on IPO delay
-- 
-- Fri Aug 10, 2007 3:19am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/10/us-mangroup-shares-idUSL1022074520070810

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Shares in Man Group ( EMG.L ) fell as much as 8.5 percent on Friday after a source said the world's largest-listed hedge fund group would delay the public offering of one of its hedge funds and on weakness in financial market. 

 Man Group was down 5.8 percent at 3:13 a.m. EDT, while Britain's FTSE 100  .FTSE  fell 1.8 percent, mirroring slides in the U.S. and Asian markets as mounting worries over the crisis in the U.S. subprime mortgage sector jolted equity markets worldwide. For a full story on the IPO delay, double click on